label.value: nasopharyngeal or oropharyngeal swab microbiology assay

definition.value: An organism detection assay that detects microorganisms in a nasopharyngeal or oropharyngeal swab specimen.
An organism detection assay that detects microorganisms in a urine specimen.

label.value: multiplex real time polymerase chain reaction assay

definition.value: A real time polymerase chain reaction assay in which multiple DNA sequences are amplified in a single cycle.

label.value: multiplex real time reverse-transcription polymerase chain reaction assay

definition.value: A real time reverse-transcription polymerase chain reaction assay in which multiple DNA sequences are amplified in a single cycle.
A device that contains blood in a membrane penetrable to mosquitoes, designed to feed mosquitoes without the need for an animal host.

An assay that evaluates host-to-mosquito transmission of a parasite organism by feeding a specimen of host blood infected with the parasite organism to a collection of mosquitoes through a mosquito membrane feeding device and, after a given time, dissecting the mosquitoes and counting the number of parasite organisms within them.
A study design that is executed primarily on a computer.

label.value: cytometric bead array assay measuring epitope specific granulysin release by T cells

definition.value: A cytometric bead array assay that detects epitope specific granulysin release by T cells.

label.value: cytometric bead array assay measuring epitope specific perforin release by T cells

definition.value: A cytometric bead array assay that detects epitope specific perforin release by T cells.
A microscopy assay that uses staining to identify acid-fast organisms in a specimen and does not require heating.
A categorical binding datum that states that there is a significant disposition of two or more entities to form a complex.

An assay that evaluates a blood specimen for antibodies currently being produced by lymphocytes in the specimen, by separating peripheral blood mononuclear cells, culturing them, and then collecting the supernatant containing the antibodies secreted from those cells.
A DNA sequencing assay that uses tyramide signal amplification (TSA) to assess distance of DNA regions to a targeted nuclear compartment or protein, typically on a scale of 100-1000 nm.
An assay for identifying DNA binding sites for a protein by fusing it to Dam methylase, and expressing it so that bound DNA gets methylated. The methylated DNA can then be isolated and analyzed.
A DNA adenine methyltransferase identification (DamID) assay in which DamID-generated DNA fragments undergo high-throughput sequencing to determine a protein's DNA-binding site.
A DNA sequencing assay in which nucleoli are isolated and the DNA associated with them is sequenced to identify nucleoli-associating domains.
A Hi-C assay in which DNase I is used for digesting DNA fragments rather than a restriction enzyme, which can result in a higher resolution of mapped chromosome contacts.
A Hi-C assay which uses micrococcal nuclease digestion in place of the restriction enzyme digestion step.

label.value: single cell combinatorial indexing Hi-C assay

definition.value: A Hi-C assay performed on massively multiplexed single-cell samples.
A Hi-C assay performed on isolated nuclei.
A Hi-C assay performed on a single cell.

A Hi-C assay in which the sample that is sequenced is derived from a collection of cells, such as a tissue sample or entire cell culture, and therefore provides results representative of the aggregate of sample cells.

A Hi-C assay that assesses interactions between multiple DNA fragments rather than only pairwise interactions as in traditional Hi-C. The experimental procedure of cross-linking, digestion, and ligation is performed similarly to traditional Hi-C, but after DNA is purified a long-read library is produced in which many ligated fragments may be contained in a single molecule. The library is then sequenced on a long read sequencer.

label.value: transposase-mediated analysis of chromatin looping assay

definition.value: A DNA sequencing assay designed to detect interacting genomic regions. Rather than the traditional Hi-C approach of digestion and proximity ligation, the procedure involves transposase-mediated insertion of an oligonucleotide linker between the pair of interacting regions.

label.value: split-pool recognition of interactions and tag extension assay

definition.value: A sequencing assay designed to detect multi-way interactions between nucleic acids. The procedure involves crosslinking nuclei, and then splitting the lysate among wells in a 96-well or other multi-well plate. A different barcode is ligated to the fragments in each well, and the lysates are pooled together again. This sequence of splitting, tagging, and re-combining is repeated several times so that fragments with the same sequences of barcodes represent fragments that have co-associated throughout the experiment. Finally, a sequencing library is constructed and high-throughput sequencing is performed.

label.value: DNA split-pool recognition of interactions and tag extension assay

definition.value: A split-pool recognition of interactions and tag extension (SPRITE) assay that only assays interactions between regions of genomic DNA.

label.value: RNA-DNA split-pool recognition of interactions and tag extension assay

definition.value: A split-pool recognition of interactions and tag extension (SPRITE) assay in which RNA in the cross-linked complexes is converted to cDNA before the initial splitting step, allowing analysis of RNA-DNA interactions.

A DNA sequencing assay designed to analyze 3D chromatin structure without relying on digestion and ligation. The procedure involves cryosectioning samples in random orientation, and then single nuclear profiles are isolated by laser microdissection. Each nuclear profile then undergoes high-throughput sequencing, and subsequent analysis can generate a matrix of inferred proximity between genomic regions.

A nuclear ligation assay for probing RNA-DNA interactions in the nucleus. Nuclei are crosslinked, and RNA fragments are ligated to proximal DNA fragments via a special linker molecule. After reverse transcription, high-throughput sequencing is performed.

label.value: assay measuring epitope specific amphiregulin production by T cells

definition.value: A T cell epitope specific cytokine production assay that detects amphiregulin production by T cells.

label.value: ELISA measuring epitope specific amphiregulin production by T cells

definition.value: An enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay that detects amphiregulin production by T cells.

label.value: perforin release during T cell degranulation

definition.value: The release of perforin during cytotoxic T cell degranulation.

label.value: granzyme A release during T cell degranulation

definition.value: The release of granzyme A during cytotoxic T cell degranulation.

label.value: granzyme B release during T cell degranulation

definition.value: The release of granzyme B during cytotoxic T cell degranulation.

label.value: granulysin release during T cell degranulation

definition.value: The release of granulysin during cytotoxic T cell degranulation.
A blood microbiology assay that detects a microorganism in a venous blood specimen.

label.value: high throughput multiplexed assay measuring binding of a B cell epitope:antibody complex

definition.value: A B cell epitope assay that measures the binding of an antibody receptor to an epitope using a high throughput multiplexed assay.

label.value: high throughput multiplexed assay measuring binding of a T cell epitope:MHC:TCR complex

definition.value: A T cell epitope assay that measures the binding of T cell receptor to an epitope using a high throughput multiplexed assay.

label.value: high throughput multiplexed assay measuring binding of a MHC:ligand complex

definition.value: A MHC ligand assay that detects the binding of a ligand to an MHC molecule using a high throughput multiplexed assay.

label.value: high throughput multiplexed assay measuring MHC ligand processing and presentation

definition.value: A MHC ligand assay that determines what ligands are processed and loaded onto MHC molecules by eluting ligands and identifying them using a high throughput multiplexed assay.

A data set that is comprised of multidimensional structured measurements and metadata required for a morphological representation of an entity. An image data set can be the source from which an image (such as a 2D image using pixels or a 3D image using voxels) is produced.
An image data set whose information content originates from some MR imaging assay and is about some MRI participant.
The subject being scanned in an MRI study, and bearor of data derived from that study.
An evaluant role that inheres in a material entity that is realized in a MR imaging assay in which MR imaging data is generated about the bearer of the evaluant role.
An image data set that encodes measurement values produced by some instrument before undergoing a data transformation.
The NMR/MRI machine protocol about the radiofrequency pulse sequence.
An image data set that is the output of an image data set analysis.

label.value: reconstructed magnetic resonance image data set

definition.value: An image data set that is the direct output of a raw magnetic resonance image data set reconstruction or a transformation of another MR image data set.

label.value: diffusion weighted magnetic resonance image data set

definition.value: A type of magnetic resonance image data set collected using at least three diffusion gradients of some factor "b," which is a function of the amplitude, duration, and interval of the gradiants.

label.value: functional magnetic resonance image data set

definition.value: An magnetic resonance image data set collected as a 4D time series representing changes in brain metabolism (i.e. BOLD), typically used as a proxy for brain activity.
